IMMEDIATE HELP

If you or someone you know is thinking about suicide, call for IMMEDIATE HELP!
24-Hour Suicide Hotline: 727-791-3131
24-Hour Mental Health Assistance: 727-541-4628​​​​​​​.

Call now

MOBILE CRISIS RESPONSE TEAM

We will come to you wherever you are; at home, school, work or storefront. Our mobile team is available 24/7 on demand and consists of licensed behavioral health therapists and psychiatrists. MCRT will provide services for individuals ages 25 and under. Our team is dispatched to the location of the crisis with a target response time of 60 minutes from the time of the call.
Call 727.362.4424 now!

VISITATION HOURS

Adults: Every day from 7 pm to 8 pm, additionally: Wednesday, Saturday and Sunday from 2 pm to 3 pm.
Kids: Every day from 7 pm to 8 pm, additionally: Wednesday, Saturday and Sunday from 2 pm to 3 pm.

COVID-19 UPDATE

All visitations are suspended.

We are requesting that those wishing to contact a family member or a friend please call 727.362.4314 or 727.362.4301 to provide your email address, so you can be contacted. After hours phone number is 727.362.4328. Sessions will be conducted via Zoom. Please, be aware that data rates may apply.

You may call as usual, to speak with your loved one by phone. 

Please bear with us during this time. We are making every effort to keep those in the facility as well as those in the community safe.

Thank you for your cooperation.

For more information please call the Department of Health (DOH): Statewide: 1-866-779-6121; Local: 727-824-6900.

we are Dedicated to mental health wellbeing

Personal Enrichment through Mental Health Services (PEMHS) has been committed to providing care in crisis since 1981. Our dedicated staff and comprehensive range of programs are designed to meet the needs of children, adults, and families to build strong communities. PEMHS is a private, non-profit behavioral health care organization located in Pinellas County, Florida. Programs include a 24-hour suicide hotline, emergency screening, and crisis intervention services, inpatient services for adults and children, and community-based programs. We understand that high-quality services are necessary to obtain the best outcome for individuals and families facing behavioral health issues. PEMHS is licensed by the Florida Department of Children and Families and by the Florida Agency for Health Care Administration. PEMHS is also certified by the American Association of Suicidology and is accredited by the Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities (CARF). PEMHS does not and shall not discriminate based on race, color, religion (creed), gender, gender expression, age, national origin (ancestry), disability, marital status, sexual orientation, or military status, in any of its activities or operations. These activities include, but are not limited to, hiring and firing of staff, selection of volunteers and vendors, and provision of services. We are committed to providing an inclusive and welcoming environment for all members of our staff, clients, volunteers, subcontractors, vendors, and clients.

DISCOVER OUR TEAM

Caring, compassionate and competent leadership

mAXINE BOOKER

CEO & pRESIDENT

zOFIA WHITING

Chief Financial Officer

Ms. Whiting has served as the organization’s VP of Finance since March of 2017 and came to PEMHS with over 20 years of accounting experience. During her 2 years at PEMHS Ms. Whiting has built a great team and positioned finance to strategically meet any new challenges that PEMHS may face going forward.

jahenein nagel

chief nursing officer

Jahenein Nagel has been employed with PEMHS for 23 years. She obtained her BSN from the University of Texas at Arlington. Ms. Nagel is currently a student at Wilkes University pursuing an MSN as a Psychiatric/Mental Health Nurse Practitioner.  As the CNO, she is responsible for planning, organizing, and directing the overall operations of Nursing/Patient Care Services and ensuring compliance with patient care quality standards.

NIKKI LABRUTO

chief clinical officer

Nikki LaBruto is a Licensed Mental Health Counselor and Qualified Supervisor. Nikki has worked at PEMHS for approximately 5 years. As CCO, she is responsible for the development, coordination, program implementation, and monitoring of all aspects of the Access Center and Recovery, IMPACT Team/Care Coordination, Mobile Crisis Response Team, and Crisis Stabilization Units clinically and administratively.

MICHELE RUSSELL

chief information officer

Michele Russell is a Technology Executive with repeated success building strong, successful organizations to meet the rapidly changing needs of the marketplace.  With over 20 years of healthcare expertise, Michele is a recognized thought leader in the health information technology community. Michele holds a BS in Information Technology and an MS in Health Informatics and Analytics.
